{
    "id": "colorutil",
    "lang": "en-US",
    "name": "ColorUtil",
    "description": "Create and read colors: ready-made presets, build from red/green/blue/opacity, convert to and from hex codes, and pull out individual channels.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/colorutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "colorutil",
        "color",
        "rgba",
        "hex"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "RenderUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/renderutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "ParticleUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/particleutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "ColorUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`ColorUtil` makes and reads **colors**. A color is built from four parts — red, green, blue, and alpha (opacity) — each from `0` to `1`. Use these tools to grab a quick preset, mix your own color, or work with hex codes like `#FF8800`."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Ready-made colors"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "The quickest option — call one and you have a color:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "Color"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Black()`", "Black."],
                ["`White()`", "White."],
                ["`Red()`", "Red."],
                ["`Green()`", "Green."],
                ["`Blue()`", "Blue."],
                ["`Transparent()`", "Fully see-through (invisible)."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Making your own color"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`FromRGBA` mixes a custom color from four numbers. Set `a` (the last value) below `1` to make it partly see-through."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// A solid orange.",
                "color orange = ColorUtil.FromRGBA(1.0, 0.5, 0.0, 1.0);",
                "",
                "// A half-transparent blue.",
                "color ghostBlue = ColorUtil.FromRGBA(0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 0.5);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Working with hex codes"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Hex codes are the `#RRGGBB` colors you see in design tools. Convert them back and forth:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`FromHTMLString(colorCode)`", "Turns a hex string like `\"#FF8800\"` into a color."],
                ["`ToHTMLString(color)`", "Turns a color back into a hex string."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "color brand = ColorUtil.FromHTMLString(\"#FF8800\");"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Reading a color's parts"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`R`, `G`, `B`, and `A` pull a single channel back out of a color (each `0`–`1`) — handy for fading or comparing colors."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "float opacity = ColorUtil.A(someColor);   // how see-through it is"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`color`", "`Black`", "—"],
                ["`color`", "`White`", "—"],
                ["`color`", "`Red`", "—"],
                ["`color`", "`Green`", "—"],
                ["`color`", "`Blue`", "—"],
                ["`color`", "`Transparent`", "—"],
                ["`color`", "`FromRGBA`", "`float r, float g, float b, float a`"],
                ["`color`", "`FromHTMLString`", "`string colorCode`"],
                ["`string`", "`ToHTMLString`", "`color color`"],
                ["`float`", "`R`", "`color color`"],
                ["`float`", "`G`", "`color color`"],
                ["`float`", "`B`", "`color color`"],
                ["`float`", "`A`", "`color color`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-018",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Colors made here are exactly what [RenderUtil's SetColor](/docs/uniscript/en-US/renderutil#block-003) and [LightUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-US/lightutil) expect — mix a color once and reuse it everywhere."
        }
    ]
}
